This paper proposes a novel approach for training sequence prediction models, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks, such as machine translation and text summarization, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a likely sub-category. The paper also introduces regularization constraints to construct bridge distributions, which is related to topics in machine learning and optimization, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed approach involves training a generator network, which is a type of neural network, and thus, the paper may also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper includes experiments that involve image captioning, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) may also be a relevant sub-category.
